1
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:38,400
<i> Dad, you need to wake up.</i>

2
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:40,733
<i>You're going back
to your family, Dad.</i>

3
00:00:40,867 --> 00:00:42,800
<i> Our family.</i>

4
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:45,833
<i>Please take care of Manuel.
We're heading to the hospital.</i>

5
00:00:45,967 --> 00:00:47,200
<i> We'll see you there.</i>

6
00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:52,567
<i> Someone blocked the road!</i>

7
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:55,400
<i>I will sue you all!
Jessica, get out of that car!</i>

8
00:00:55,533 --> 00:00:56,333
<i> Jessica,</i>

9
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:59,167
<i> hold dad, okay!</i>

10
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,433
<i> Dad, hold on!</i>

11
00:01:04,633 --> 00:01:06,200
<i> Mr. Manuel, welcome back.</i>

12
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:07,233
<i> How are you?</i>

13
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:10,467
<i>Doc, can you please
let Jessica in?</i>

14
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:11,833
<i>I just have something
to tell her.</i>

15
00:01:11,967 --> 00:01:13,233
<i> Thank you so much</i>

16
00:01:13,367 --> 00:01:15,533
<i>for not leaving me since
the very beginning.</i>

17
00:01:15,667 --> 00:01:18,700
<i>I love you. I love you.
I love you, Dad.</i>

18
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,233
<i> I love you so much.</i>

19
00:01:20,367 --> 00:01:22,133
<i> I'll remember that, Dad.</i>

20
00:01:22,267 --> 00:01:23,767
<i> We need to talk.</i>

21
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,367
<i> What is your problem?</i>

22
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:27,500
<i> Jessica, you're so selfish!</i>

23
00:01:27,633 --> 00:01:31,533
<i>Didn't you even think something
bad could've happened to him?</i>

24
00:01:31,667 --> 00:01:34,400
<i>Jessica, is that what
a daughter does?</i>

25
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:36,333
<i>It's like you're not even
dad's child!</i>

26
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:43,467
I am dad's daughter, Coleen.
I am his daughter!

27
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:49,300
Don't you ever say that
I'm not his child.

28
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:51,100
No matter what happens,

29
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:53,367
I am and will always be his
daughter.

30
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:54,933
Fine.

31
00:01:55,067 --> 00:01:56,867
You're my father's daughter.

32
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,167
Do you need to repeat it?

33
00:01:58,300 --> 00:01:59,367
Yes!

34
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:02,900
So it sinks into your head
that I'm daddy's youngest,

35
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:04,533
not just you.

36
00:02:04,667 --> 00:02:08,400
And don't you dare erase me
from his life, Coleen.

37
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:10,533
Because I'm his daughter, too.

38
00:02:11,867 --> 00:02:14,233
And that makes me your sister.

39
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,633
No, Jessica.

40
00:02:16,767 --> 00:02:18,700
I don't want you as my sister.

41
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:23,933
You think I want to be
your sister?

42
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:28,700
I no longer want to be with you
because you're fake!

43
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,500
You call me fake?

44
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:35,833
I'm telling you straight to your
face that I don't like you

45
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:38,400
because you're a stealer.

46
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:41,033
You stole dad away from me.

47
00:02:41,167 --> 00:02:43,733
Then you went after mom.

48
00:02:43,867 --> 00:02:46,033
And now, you're trying to take
my brother Jeffrey

49
00:02:46,167 --> 00:02:49,267
and my sister Andrea, too!

50
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:51,433
I'm not taking them away
from you.

51
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:59,900
I just want to be close to them,
like we used to be, Coleen.

52
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:04,667
You're just too jealous
and insecure!

53
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,900
I am not insecure about you!

54
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:08,167
Yes, you are.

55
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:28,900
Jessica!

56
00:03:29,033 --> 00:03:31,400
Where are you? Brace yourself.
You betrayed me!

57
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:36,367
You know what, Jessica?

58
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:39,033
I wish I had never met you!

59
00:03:39,167 --> 00:03:42,467
I wish I had never allowed you
to meet dad!

60
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,500
So now the truth comes out!

61
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:47,633
You just want him all
to yourself!

62
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:51,333
You want to keep him away
from me!

63
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:55,067
I wish you'd just disappear!

64
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:57,367
So that my family would finally
be happy!

65
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:01,100
Disappear?

66
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:07,767
Coleen, you want me gone just so
you can have dad to yourself?

67
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:09,933
That's not what I meant!

68
00:04:10,767 --> 00:04:12,333
No!

69
00:04:12,467 --> 00:04:14,600
No, that's what you meant.

70
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:17,467
You want me dead, Coleen.

71
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:20,667
You want me gone so you won't
have to share anymore.

72
00:04:24,967 --> 00:04:29,767
That's the cruelest thing anyone
has ever said to me, Coleen.

73
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:35,100
And coming from you,
my own sister.

74
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:42,300
I never thought the person who'd
tell me to die would be you.

75
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,133
<i>Hello there,
Miss Felma and Coleen.</i>

76
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:53,300
<i>Jessica, can you tell dad
that I'm always thinking of him</i>

77
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:56,200
<i>and that I'm always praying
for him?</i>

78
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:57,300
<i> Of course.</i>

79
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:00,067
<i> Coleen.</i>

80
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,200
<i> Jessica.</i>

81
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:03,067
<i> Dad?</i>

82
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,000
<i> Coleen, my dear?</i>

83
00:05:04,133 --> 00:05:05,233
<i> Dad!</i>

84
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:07,567
<i> Dad!</i>

85
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:10,167
<i> Jessica.</i>

86
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,733
<i>Didang, help me bring them
inside through the back.</i>

87
00:05:15,867 --> 00:05:17,800
<i>Jessica, these are some
of my clothes.</i>

88
00:05:17,933 --> 00:05:19,467
<i> They should fit you.</i>

89
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,567
<i> Thank you, Coleen.</i>

90
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:23,200
<i> Dance with dad tonight, okay?</i>

91
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,667
Jessica...

92
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,133
Jessica, I'm sorry.

93
00:05:39,267 --> 00:05:40,900
Jessica, please. I'm sorry.

94
00:05:41,033 --> 00:05:42,400
- I'm sorry.
- No, Coleen.

95
00:05:42,533 --> 00:05:44,033
That's not what I meant,
Jessica, please...

96
00:05:44,167 --> 00:05:45,467
I swear,
that's not what I meant!

97
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:48,600
- No!
- Jessica, please, I'm so sorry!

98
00:05:48,733 --> 00:05:50,733
Please, Jessica! Please!

99
00:05:50,867 --> 00:05:52,800
During the trip,
dad seemed fine.

100
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:53,800
He was so talkative.

101
00:05:53,933 --> 00:05:55,633
Uncle even had to tell him
to quiet down.

102
00:05:55,767 --> 00:05:57,700
Maybe he got too excited
to see all of us.

103
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:58,967
He suddenly got stronger

104
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:01,800
because he managed to escape
the clutches of that witch.

105
00:06:01,933 --> 00:06:04,933
- Please, Jessica!
- No!

106
00:06:05,067 --> 00:06:06,933
- Hey!
- Let go of me!

107
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:14,133
Was that Hazel?

108
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,933
That sounded like Jessica!

109
00:06:20,067 --> 00:06:22,233
Wasn't that Coleen's voice?

110
00:06:26,267 --> 00:06:27,167
What now?

111
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,733
No! Don't stop me!

112
00:06:30,533 --> 00:06:31,167
That was Coleen!

113
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,667
- Coleen!
- Coleen!

114
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,467
Coleen?

115
00:06:35,367 --> 00:06:36,367
Yeah.

116
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:39,767
I have to go.

117
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,100
What's going on?

118
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:47,800
Please stop!

119
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,400
No!

120
00:06:51,533 --> 00:06:56,333
I haven't gotten even yet
with what you did to my child!

121
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,433
- Enough!
- No!

122
00:06:57,567 --> 00:06:58,600
Ouch!

123
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:07,533
Are you two fighting again?

124
00:07:07,667 --> 00:07:09,400
Can't you just make peace
already?

125
00:07:09,533 --> 00:07:10,233
What are you doing?

126
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:11,367
Jessica!

127
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,100
Stay out of this!

128
00:07:15,267 --> 00:07:16,900
Jeffrey!

129
00:07:17,533 --> 00:07:19,400
That's enough!

130
00:07:19,533 --> 00:07:22,267
- No! Please stop!
- Let go of me!

131
00:07:24,667 --> 00:07:26,600
Mom! Enough!

132
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:28,567
Enough!

133
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,500
All you do is fight!

134
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:35,833
All you bring is trouble!

135
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:37,900
Jessica!

136
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:39,300
Jessica, wait!

137
00:07:40,533 --> 00:07:42,433
- Jessica! Jessica!
- I'm done!

138
00:07:42,567 --> 00:07:44,133
I just want to go home!

139
00:07:44,267 --> 00:07:45,933
Jessica, please wait.

140
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:47,133
I just want to go home!

141
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,167
Jessica, wait!

142
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:49,333
Jessica, please!

143
00:07:49,467 --> 00:07:50,767
Let go of me, Coleen!
Just let go!

144
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:53,567
Jessica, please, let's talk.
I'm sorry. Please.

145
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,833
No! You want me gone, right?

146
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:57,100
Fine! I'm leaving!

147
00:07:57,233 --> 00:07:58,200
I don't want to see
any of you ever again!

148
00:07:58,333 --> 00:07:59,433
Jessica, no!

149
00:07:59,567 --> 00:08:00,233
What are you doing?

150
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:01,300
Jessica, please!

151
00:08:01,433 --> 00:08:03,533
I realized my mistake!
I'm sorry.

152
00:08:03,667 --> 00:08:05,733
Let's talk about this, Jessica!

153
00:08:05,867 --> 00:08:08,300
- Coleen, stop! No!
- Jessica, please!

154
00:08:08,433 --> 00:08:09,500
Jessica!

155
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:11,333
Jessica!

156
00:08:13,967 --> 00:08:16,567
Jessica!

157
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,500
Oh my God! The girl!

158
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:31,233
Jessica! Jessica!

159
00:08:36,767 --> 00:08:39,367
Jessica!

160
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:45,033
Please, help my sister!
Somebody help us!

161
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:46,433
Jessica!

162
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:48,533
Please help us!

163
00:08:48,667 --> 00:08:54,500
Please help us! Call a doctor!
Please! Jessica!

164
00:08:56,100 --> 00:08:57,133
<i> Okay.</i>

165
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:59,333
Good progress.

166
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:01,433
You're not having a hard time,
right, Manuel?

167
00:09:01,567 --> 00:09:03,000
Not at all, Doctor.

168
00:09:03,133 --> 00:09:05,800
Okay. We'll move you
to a regular room.

169
00:09:05,933 --> 00:09:08,000
But you still need close
monitoring, okay?

170
00:09:08,133 --> 00:09:09,300
Okay, Doc.

171
00:09:09,433 --> 00:09:10,367
<i> Okay.</i>

172
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:14,767
Right now fixing your admitting
orders for the regular room.

173
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,533
In a bit,
you can be transferred.

174
00:09:17,667 --> 00:09:19,000
Thank you, Doctor.

175
00:09:20,067 --> 00:09:22,167
So, what the doctor said
is true?

176
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:25,367
You suddenly felt stronger?

177
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:28,700
Yes, Felma.

178
00:09:30,567 --> 00:09:33,400
You know, I really feel stronger
whenever I'm with you.

179
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:37,467
Felma, you are my strength.

180
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,800
You and our children.

181
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:42,900
Psychosomatic.

182
00:09:43,033 --> 00:09:45,700
Good emotions really trigger
good healing.

183
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:47,467
All right, I'll leave you two
alone.

184
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,867
Thank you, Doctor.

185
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,933
Ouch! It hurts!

186
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,167
Let go of me, Abel!
Let go of me!

187
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:06,433
- Why are you interfering here?
- A child got hit!

188
00:10:06,567 --> 00:10:08,033
Hazel!

189
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:09,367
Jessica?

190
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:11,000
- Jessica!
- Hazel!

191
00:10:11,133 --> 00:10:11,867
Hazel!

192
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:12,767
Coleen!

193
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:14,933
Coleen! Coleen!

194
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,967
Jessica!

195
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:20,767
Jessica, please wake up!

196
00:10:21,067 --> 00:10:22,000
Jessica!

197
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,700
Help!

198
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:27,300
It's Jessica! Wake up!
Jessica, please!

199
00:10:27,433 --> 00:10:29,133
We're going to the hospital,
please!

200
00:10:29,267 --> 00:10:32,233
Jessica, please wake up!
You need to see a doctor!

201
00:10:32,367 --> 00:10:34,200
Help!

202
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:35,467
Jessica, please, let's talk!

203
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:39,700
- Jessica! Jessica! My God!
- Help!

204
00:10:39,967 --> 00:10:46,400
Jessica! Jessica!

205
00:10:46,533 --> 00:10:47,767
Oh my God, Jessica!

206
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:49,167
- What did you do?
- Nothing!

207
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:52,367
- What happened?
- Nothing, nothing!

208
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:54,400
- Jessica!
- Coleen!

209
00:10:55,767 --> 00:10:56,967
Come on, come on, come on...

210
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:00,633
Oh my God, Jessica!

211
00:11:03,633 --> 00:11:10,267
- No! Jessica!
- Help! Call!

212
00:11:10,433 --> 00:11:11,533
Ambulance!

213
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:15,000
- Call an ambulance!
- Help! Dear, hang in there!

214
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:20,733
Help! Jessica! Jessica, dear!
My God! Where is it?

215
00:11:20,867 --> 00:11:30,767
Hurry! Jessica! Call them!
Dear! Hurry! Hurry up!

216
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:40,867
- Jessica!
- Jessica!

217
00:11:44,733 --> 00:11:47,600
Dear, hang in there.

218
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:58,400
God really is good.

219
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:03,133
He gave us a chance to be
together again.

220
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:05,700
You know, Felma, I thought we'd
never see each other again.

221
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:09,733
Manuel, did Hazel make you sign

222
00:12:09,867 --> 00:12:13,500
a Discharge Against Medical
Advice form?

223
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:18,133
No, only the one for the health
insurance.

224
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:22,100
She forged your signature.
That's how she got you out.

225
00:12:22,233 --> 00:12:25,233
That woman doesn't care at all.

226
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:27,400
Even if your life
were in danger,

227
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:29,733
she'd do whatever to get you
away from us.

228
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:32,067
Hazel is such a monster.

229
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:34,767
Once I recover,

230
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:37,333
I'll file an illegal detention
case against her.

231
00:12:37,467 --> 00:12:41,033
And Attorney Yeban and I will
also file the annulment case.

232
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:43,033
Manuel, don't stress yourself.

233
00:12:43,167 --> 00:12:47,033
I'm sorry I brought up the fake
signature.

234
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:51,800
Where do you think the kids are?

235
00:12:53,233 --> 00:12:55,467
They haven't even checked in.

236
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,300
Maybe they just stepped out
to buy something.

237
00:12:57,433 --> 00:12:59,967
They probably thought I'd be
stuck in the ER for a while.

238
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:03,567
I'll text them
as soon as you're in the room.

239
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:06,133
Do you think Jessica
is with them?

240
00:13:06,267 --> 00:13:07,767
Most likely.

241
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:10,600
She's okay with Jeff now, right?

242
00:13:10,733 --> 00:13:12,633
Andrea's fine with her, too.

243
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:14,267
Only Coleen is the problem.

244
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,567
I hope they make up.

245
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:20,600
If they still don't, I'll sit
them down until they make up.

246
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:22,067
And if they still don't
reconcile,

247
00:13:22,233 --> 00:13:24,333
I'll really give them
a good beating.

248
00:13:24,667 --> 00:13:26,633
This is exhausting. It's the
same thing over and over.

249
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:28,200
Oh, here it is. Come on.

250
00:13:38,867 --> 00:13:39,833
Jessica!

251
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:42,267
Jessica!

252
00:13:42,667 --> 00:13:46,567
We're almost at the ER, dear.
Okay? Hang in there. Dear.

253
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:52,567
Dear, we're almost there.
Almost there.

254
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:53,567
Status?

255
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,733
Severe maxillofacial
trauma, Doctor.

256
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:59,733
Positive for intracranial
bleeding, abdominal hemorrhage,

257
00:13:59,867 --> 00:14:01,933
and a closed left femur
fracture.

258
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:04,700
<i> GCS-11, E-324, B2M6.</i>

259
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,633
<i>Doctor, her facial bones
are broken,</i>

260
00:14:06,767 --> 00:14:08,167
<i>so she's having difficulty
speaking.</i>

261
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:10,033
Prepare for an emergency
exploratory laparotomy.

262
00:14:10,167 --> 00:14:11,333
- Yes, Doctor.
- Is the blood ready?

263
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:12,667
Yes, Doctor.

264
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:15,933
Page the anesthesiologist and
the neurosurgeon on duty now.

265
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:17,133
Yes, Doctor.

266
00:14:17,267 --> 00:14:19,067
Jessica, sweetheart.

267
00:14:21,067 --> 00:14:22,500
Mommy is here.

268
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,467
Nurse Glo, please. Let me in.
I'm a nurse, too.

269
00:14:28,633 --> 00:14:29,900
I know what to do.

270
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:32,500
Sorry, Nurse Hazel.

271
00:14:32,633 --> 00:14:34,233
You know the protocol.
You can only go this far.

272
00:14:34,367 --> 00:14:36,600
Wait a moment. I'm a nurse, too.
I know what to do.

273
00:14:36,733 --> 00:14:37,700
I won't interfere.

274
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:38,533
I just want to be there
by my daughter's side.

275
00:14:38,667 --> 00:14:39,167
We'll take care
of your daughter.

276
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,767
Wait, Nurse Glo!

277
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:42,967
Sweetheart, Jessica,
mommy's right here.

278
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:06,767
Coleen, sweetheart.

279
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:09,867
Are you ready to share
what happened?

280
00:15:21,533 --> 00:15:22,833
I was holding her.

281
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,200
I was holding her.

282
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,500
I was holding her.

283
00:15:28,633 --> 00:15:31,700
I was holding her.

284
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,667
I didn't mean it.

285
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:34,833
No...

286
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,167
I didn't mean it.

287
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:41,033
I didn't mean it.

288
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:46,867
I didn't mean it.

289
00:15:49,733 --> 00:15:51,733
I'm sorry.

290
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:57,367
I didn't mean it.

291
00:16:06,167 --> 00:16:09,833
Not a single one of them
even replied.

292
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,000
Are they with Jessica?

293
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,267
- Miss Felma, hi.
- Doctor.

294
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:23,233
He's asleep.

295
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:25,033
- Is everything okay?
- Yes.

296
00:16:25,167 --> 00:16:27,433
All right.
How's he doing, nurse?

297
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:28,633
Please check.

298
00:16:28,767 --> 00:16:30,967
Are the vitals from earlier
okay?

299
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,733
Doctor, all vitals are good.

300
00:16:36,867 --> 00:16:38,933
Okay. Please show me the chart.

301
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:48,700
Okay. Good. Good.

302
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:53,533
Let's do VS Q2.
Same IV to continue.

303
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:55,233
Continue the Piptaz.

304
00:16:55,367 --> 00:16:57,600
If he stays stable for the next
24 hours,

305
00:16:57,733 --> 00:16:59,933
we'll check vitals every
4 hours.

306
00:17:00,067 --> 00:17:00,900
- Okay.
- Yes, Doc. Okay.

307
00:17:01,033 --> 00:17:02,400
Manuel is good.

308
00:17:02,533 --> 00:17:03,200
Okay?

309
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:05,100
- Thank you, Doctor.
- Okay.

310
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,900
What happened?

311
00:17:11,033 --> 00:17:14,400
What happened?
Tell us so we can understand.

312
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:17,833
You have to say it, okay?

313
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:18,767
Andrea.

314
00:17:20,867 --> 00:17:24,233
Andrea, maybe we shouldn't
push her.

315
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:26,267
It's still too hard for her.

316
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:30,833
Sorry, dear.

317
00:17:32,667 --> 00:17:33,533
Mom's calling.

318
00:17:35,267 --> 00:17:38,667
What should I say?
Should I tell her?

319
00:17:42,667 --> 00:17:44,000
Tell her the truth.

320
00:17:44,133 --> 00:17:46,267
We need to tell her
what happened.

321
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,500
Wait, darling. No, not yet.

322
00:17:49,667 --> 00:17:52,633
If we tell Felma,
she'll tell Manuel.

323
00:17:52,767 --> 00:17:57,167
He might have a heart attack.
No, no, no.

324
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:59,967
Jeffrey, I agree with Aunt Paz.

325
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:03,300
Maybe it's better not to say
anything yet.

326
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:05,333
Your dad might be shocked.

327
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:12,733
Hello, Mom?

328
00:18:12,867 --> 00:18:16,567
Jeffrey, why didn't you answer
my texts?

329
00:18:17,667 --> 00:18:20,333
Your father has already been
moved to the regular room.

330
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:22,333
Where are you, kids?

331
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:26,700
Mom, we'll go home with Coleen
and Andrea first.

332
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:28,400
We'll get you some stuff.

333
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:31,900
Since dad will be staying here
a few days, right?

334
00:18:32,033 --> 00:18:33,667
You'll watch over him, right?

335
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:34,800
<i> Oh, yeah.</i>

336
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:37,333
Good thinking.

337
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,300
Thank you.

338
00:18:40,433 --> 00:18:41,833
Okay, Mom. Take care.

339
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:48,533
Andrea, message Didang.
Tell her to send mom's things.

340
00:18:48,667 --> 00:18:51,700
Probably enough for 2 to 3 days.
Have her deliver it.

341
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:52,900
Okay, okay.

342
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:56,500
Uncle, Auntie...

343
00:18:58,333 --> 00:19:00,333
You can go see mom
and dad first.

344
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,267
<i> Okay, we will.</i>

345
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,567
But...

346
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:06,700
when do we tell them?

347
00:19:10,133 --> 00:19:13,067
Uncle, should we tell them now?

348
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:19,500
I think it's better to make sure
Jessica is okay first.

349
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:21,767
What matters most right now
is her condition.

350
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:30,733
I'll just go to the OR
and check her status, okay?

351
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:31,800
I'll go with you.

352
00:19:31,933 --> 00:19:32,600
Me, too.

353
00:19:33,833 --> 00:19:36,567
I'll come too.

354
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:38,367
Are you sure, dear?

355
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:43,367
Uncle, Auntie,
we'll go there for now.

356
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:44,767
- All right, all right.
- We'll go now.

357
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,333
It feels like it was just
yesterday I was here.

358
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:04,100
Manuel was inside then...

359
00:20:06,167 --> 00:20:07,933
now it's Jessica.

360
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,700
What will happen next?

361
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:12,700
Alice,

362
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:15,133
maybe...

363
00:20:17,433 --> 00:20:20,033
will it be my turn?

364
00:20:20,167 --> 00:20:20,867
But...

365
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,467
if that happens,

366
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:30,433
will Manuel and Jessica
still be here for me?

367
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:34,300
Or...

368
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:38,033
maybe they'll be with Felma's
family?

369
00:20:39,133 --> 00:20:40,633
Celebrating.

370
00:20:42,233 --> 00:20:45,267
Hoping I won't survive...

371
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,333
Is that it?

372
00:20:46,467 --> 00:20:48,133
Is that next, Alice?

373
00:20:49,133 --> 00:20:51,000
Enough, friend.

374
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:53,233
Stop imagining all that.

375
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:58,767
Jessica!

376
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:03,533
Alice.

377
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:06,867
Alice, what's happening
to Jessica?

378
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,533
What?

379
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:10,200
I don't know, but...

380
00:21:13,067 --> 00:21:14,267
I have a really bad feeling

381
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,700
something's happening
to Jessica.

382
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:20,467
Alice.

383
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:23,833
Let's see Jessica.

384
00:21:25,233 --> 00:21:28,300
- No. Calm down, friend.
- Jessica.

385
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:35,433
Doc, we're losing her.

386
00:21:35,567 --> 00:21:36,400
<i> EP.</i>

387
00:21:38,167 --> 00:21:39,467
Charge to 160.

388
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:45,933
Clear.

389
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,033
<i> Clear.</i>

390
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:53,667
Start CPR.

391
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:00,300
Rhythm check.

392
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:03,900
Charge to 250.

393
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:05,700
Start CPR.

394
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,300
Jessica.

395
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:20,967
Something bad is happening
to Jessica.

396
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:21,767
Friend...

397
00:22:22,067 --> 00:22:23,333
Friend, stay calm.

398
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:25,800
Jessica is in good hands.

399
00:22:26,267 --> 00:22:29,667
We're at Southcrest.
The people here are excellent.

400
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,700
The doctors are excellent.

401
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:32,900
Jessica.

402
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:35,367
CPR.

403
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:41,100
Rhythm check.

404
00:22:44,133 --> 00:22:45,567
Charge to 350.

405
00:22:48,767 --> 00:22:49,633
Clear.

406
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,367
Begin CPR.

407
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,667
What is it that you're not
telling me?

408
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,867
Are you waiting for me
to get angry?

409
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,033
Mom, can you not tell dad
just yet?

410
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,500
So you're here.

411
00:23:20,633 --> 00:23:23,300
Where did you get that criminal
streak from?

412
00:23:25,667 --> 00:23:27,733
Mom! Stop it!

413
00:23:27,867 --> 00:23:32,233
Dad, maybe we can make this
real?

414
00:23:32,367 --> 00:23:35,967
We'll make our family real.

415
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:38,400
There's one more thing
I wish for.

416
00:23:38,533 --> 00:23:40,400
If it's possible,

417
00:23:40,533 --> 00:23:43,033
could you also treat Jessica
like family?

418
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:46,433
You're defending your daughter?

419
00:23:46,567 --> 00:23:48,300
After what she did to mine?

420
00:23:48,433 --> 00:23:50,000
What did she do?

421
00:23:50,133 --> 00:23:51,733
Coleen, admit it.

422
00:23:51,867 --> 00:23:53,633
You pushed Jessica,

423
00:23:53,767 --> 00:23:55,467
and that's why she got hit
by the car!

424
00:23:55,633 --> 00:23:56,933
What happened?

425
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,767
What happened?

426
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:02,867
I will not forgive
what they did to you.

427
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,667
So wake up.

428
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,367
I want you to see
what I will do to her.
